<p><span class="bold">Drink or Die</span> the famous and originally Russian group are known for three different reasons.
</p>
The first is that back in 1995 they publicly released Microsoft's Windows 95 weeks before it's official release date (though some other groups did as well, it was DOD who received the mainstream rap for it).
<p></p>
It is also known for being the publisher of the first utility that successfully by-passed the DVD CSS protection system. Enabling people to rip DVDs to their computers for the very first time.
<p></p>
Finally Drink or Die is the group that was eventually taken down in 2001 by the well publicised FBI Operation known as Buccaneer.
<p></p>
If you want to find out more about the DOD application <span class="underline">DVD Speed Ripper</span> and DeCSS, we have a <a href="groups/dod/more+dod_decss.txt">text file detailing it's history</a>.
