"The glorious Drink Or Die label started in the end of April, 1993, in one Moscow flat by Deviator. This DOD thing flashed in his mind and he decided to take this name to build his own underground computer empire. He called his comrade Baphomet and offered his plan. This point marks the beginning of the DOD Legacy. For the first couple of months, DOD was busy exploring the scene and feeling out the competition. Also trying to find it's place among many American and European teams. Soon, Deviator renamed himself to the now infamous Jimmy Jamez in the summer of 1993. The first official release of DOD occurred in May, 1993 and was called License User Crack for PCBoard 15.0 (cracked by DOD old skool - Trasher). Actually, most group's first releases were dedicated to PCBoard users. It was the time of PPE's and PPE groups and DOD easily took a good share in this "market". For the first 6-7 months DOD was strictly RUSSIAN and no foreign dudes were taken into the group at all. This policy finally changed when Jimmy Jamez and Baphomet developed some relations with Dutch and German pirates. Silverado BBS (4 nodes) joined DOD as Dutch HQ and Sewers of Darkness BBS (2 nodes) in Germany as a Courier HQ. People all over the world started to see DOD releases on their boards regularly. Besides awesome PPE work. DOD concentrated on cracking and releasing trainers for games.
<p></p>
